  "texts": [
    "The proposed GPA-BERT Fig. 2 | Comparative analysis of prediction performance between GPA-GCN and others.",
    "a, b The effect of k-NN for the prediction performance of GPA-GCN on two tasks, where the abscissa axis represents the number of neighbors.",
    "c, d The comparison of GPA-GCN with the classic machine learning methods on two tasks, including DNN (deep learning-based deep neural network), DT (decision tree), ERT (extremely randomized tree), GNBs (Gaussian naïve Bayes), RF (Random forest), and SGD (Stochastic Gradient Descent).",
    "e, f The comparison of GPA-GCN with the traditional GCN method on two tasks.",
    "Acc, Pre, Rec, F1, AUC, and AUPR represent the accuracy, precision, recall, F1score, the area under the receiver operating characteristic curve, and the area under the precisionrecall curve, respectively."
  ]
